ood, E.F., Burges, S.J., A simple hydrologically based model of land surface water and energy fluxes for general circulation models (1994) J. Geophys. Res., 99 (D7), pp. 14415-14428; Mantua, N.J., Hare, S.R., Zhang, Y., Wallace, J.M., Francis, R.C., A Pacific interdecadal climate oscillation with impacts on salmon production (1997) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 78, pp. 1069-1079; Meehl, G.A., Hu, A., Santer, B.D., The mid-1970s climate shift in the Pacific and the relative roles of forced versus inherent decadal variability (2009) J. Climate, 22, pp. 780-792; Minder, J.R., The sensitivity of mountain snowpack accumulation to climate warming (2010) J. Climate, 23, pp. 2634-2650; Mote, P.W., Trends in snow water equivalent in the Pacific Northwest and their climatic causes (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30, p. 1601. , doi:10.1029/2003GL017258; Mote, P.W., Climate-driven variability and trends in mountain snowpack in westernNorthAmerica (2006) J. Climate, 19, pp. 6209-6220; Mote, P.W., Hamlet, A.F., Clark, M.P., Lettenmaier, D.P., Declining mountain snowpack in western North America (2005) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 86, pp. 39-49; Mote, P.W., Hamlet, A.F., Salathé, E., Has spring snowpack declined in theWashingtonCascades? Hydrol (2008) Earth Syst. Sci., 12, pp. 193-206; Overland, J.E., Wang, M., Future climate of the North Pacific Ocean (2007) Eos, Trans. Amer. Geophys. Union, 88. , doi:10.1029/2007EO160003; Panofsky, H.A., Brier, G.W., (1963) Some Applications of Statistics to Meteorology, p. 224. , The Pennsylvania State University; Pierce, D.W., Attribution of declining western U. S. snowpack to human effects (2008) J. Climate, 21, pp. 6425-6444; Regonda, S.K., Rajagopalan, B., Clark, M., Pitlick, J., Seasonal cycle shifts in hydroclimatology over the western United States (2005) J. Climate, 18, pp. 372-384; Slack, J.R., Landwehr, J.M., Hydro-climatic data network (HCDN): A U.S. Geological Survey streamflow data set for the United States for the study of climate variations